## Step 3 – Configure the Edge Firewall (Router)

This router acts as your firewall, separating the internal network from the internet.

```
enable
configure terminal
hostname Edge-Firewall

! WAN interface (facing ISP)
interface FastEthernet0/0
 ip address 203.0.113.2 255.255.255.252
 ip nat outside
 no shutdown

! LAN interface (facing Core Switch)
interface FastEthernet0/1
 ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
 ip nat inside
 no shutdown
exit
```

### 3.1 – Static Route to the Internet

```
ip route 0.0.0.0 0.0.0.0 203.0.113.1
```

### 3.2 – Static Route to Internal VLANs

```
ip route 10.10.10.0 255.255.255.0 192.168.1.254
ip route 10.10.20.0 255.255.255.0 192.168.1.254
ip route 10.10.30.0 255.255.255.0 192.168.1.254
```

### 3.3 – NAT (to allow internal users to reach internet)

```
access-list 1 permit 10.10.0.0 0.0.255.255
ip nat inside source list 1 interface FastEthernet0/0 overload
```

### 3.4 – Basic Firewall ACL (Block inbound traffic from internet)

```
! Extended ACL to block unsolicited inbound traffic
ip access-list extended BLOCK-INBOUND
 permit tcp any host 10.10.30.10 eq 80    ! Allow HTTP to Web Server
 permit tcp any host 10.10.30.10 eq 443   ! Allow HTTPS to Web Server
 deny   ip any any                         ! Block everything else inbound

interface FastEthernet0/0
 ip access-group BLOCK-INBOUND in
exit
```

