## Step 4 – Apply ACLs on the Core Switch

### 4.1 – Restrict Management Access (Standard ACL)

Only the Admin PC (10.10.10.10) should be able to manage network devices.

```
ip access-list standard MGMT-ONLY
 permit 10.10.10.0 0.0.0.255
 deny   any

line vty 0 4
 access-class MGMT-ONLY in
 login local
 transport input ssh
exit
```

### 4.2 – Restrict Users from Accessing Servers Directly (Extended ACL)

Users can access the Web Server on port 80/443 but nothing else on the SERVERS VLAN.

```
ip access-list extended USERS-TO-SERVERS
 permit tcp 10.10.20.0 0.0.0.255 10.10.30.0 0.0.0.255 eq 80
 permit tcp 10.10.20.0 0.0.0.255 10.10.30.0 0.0.0.255 eq 443
 deny   ip 10.10.20.0 0.0.0.255 10.10.30.0 0.0.0.255
 permit ip any any

interface vlan 20
 ip access-group USERS-TO-SERVERS in
exit
```

### 4.3 – Block USERS from accessing MGMT VLAN

```
ip access-list extended BLOCK-USERS-MGMT
 deny   ip 10.10.20.0 0.0.0.255 10.10.10.0 0.0.0.255
 permit ip any any

interface vlan 20
 ip access-group BLOCK-USERS-MGMT in
exit
```

> ⚠️ Note: Only one ACL per interface per direction. Combine rules into one ACL if needed.

